On Sat, 27 Apr 2002 java1972bg(-at-)aol.com wrote:

> Question is, on a 1971 bus the 1600 size engine, how many shims is to many.
> Or just check end play and slap them in till good. The bus we just bought was
> dumping oil so out the engine came checked end play and other things but it
> looks as though there is about 1/16inch space. I don;t have  a true gauge but
> what do you think.

You need three shims, but the thickness of those shims is important.  I'd
suggest that you consult the Bentley manual and consider the problem
carefuly before proceeding.  End play is measured in thousandths of an
inch and if you get it wrong you are in a world of hurt.

George Lyle

